_id":"ast-parents@0.0.1","dist":{"shasum":"508fd0f05d0c48775d9eccda2e174423261e8dd3","tarball":"https://registry.npmjs.org/ast-parents/-/ast-parents-0.0.1.tgz","integrity":"sha512-XHusKxKz3zoYk1ic8Un640joHbFMhbqneyoZfoKnEGtf2ey9Uh/IdpcQplODdO/kENaMIWsD0nJm4+wX3UNLHA==","signatures":[{"keyid":"SHA256:jl3bwswu80PjjokCgh0o2w5c2U4LhQAE57gj9cz1kzA","sig":"MEUCIGmSSDTa3H2OyGgiwD5gABEPBLCOjAw4dBsaOxtvnvzlAiEAyOn0mx8Ndc09vMSFks6cMc/mnsJZJjBej8jeiurxRRI="}]},"_from":".","_npmVersion":"1.3.25","_npmUser":{"name":"hughsk","email":"hughskennedy@gmail.com"},"maintainers":[{"name":"hughsk","email":"hughskennedy@gmail.com"}]}},"readme":"# ast-parents [![Flattr this!](https://api.flattr.com/button/flattr-badge-large.png)](https://flattr.com/submit/auto?user_id=hughskennedy&url=http://github.com/hughsk/ast-parents&title=ast-parents&description=hughsk/ast-parents%20on%20GitHub&language=en_GB&tags=flattr,github,javascript&category=software)[![experimental](http://hughsk.github.io/stability-badges/dist/experimental.svg)](http://github.com/hughsk/stability-badges) #\n\nWalks a JavaScript AST, such as one supplied via\n[esprima](http://github.com/ariya/esprima), and adds a `parent`\nproperty to each node.\n\nMakes it much easier to navigate the AST, and the `parent` properties\nadded here are non-enumerable so you can still serialize the tree to JSON\nwithout `JSON.stringify` throwing an error.\n\n## Usage ##\n\n[![ast-parents](https://nodei.co/npm/ast-parents.png?mini=true)](https://nodei.co/npm/ast-parents)\n\n`require('ast-parents')(ast)`\n\nWhere `ast` is an AST object. For example:\n\n``` javascript\nvar esprima = require('esprima')\nvar fs = require('fs')\n\nvar src = fs.readFileSync(__filename, 'utf8')\nvar ast = esprima.parse(src)\n\nparents(ast)\n\nast.body[0].parent === ast.body\n```\n\n## License ##\n\nMIT. See [LICENSE.md](http://github.com/hughsk/ast-parents/blob/master/LICENSE.md) for details.\n","maintainers":[{"name":"hughsk","email":"hughskennedy@gmail.com"}],"time":{"mo